澎湃新闻记者 高丹环球网最近，日本送来的抗疫物资上频频引经据典——有取自日本国长屋王偈子的“山川异域，风月同天”，有取自《诗经·秦风·无衣》的“岂曰无衣，与子同裳”，最近的一批物资上的文字则引用了唐代诗人王昌龄《送柴侍御》中的一句“青山一道同雲雨，明月何曾是两鄕”，甚至还化用《千字文》中的“同气连枝”写作了一首小诗——“辽河雪融，富山花开；同气连枝，共盼春来。
In this poem, I read in agatha, "Sagittarius of the mountain and the moon in agatha," I say, "I have no clothes, I am in love with my son." The latest batch of materials contains the phrase "Ai mountain with rain, bright moon is two quilts."
”日本援助武汉↓山川异域，风月同天首都师范大学文学院教授、中国古代文学博士生导师邓小军在接受澎湃新闻的采访时谈及：由鉴真称道的日本国长屋王造千袈裟，来施中华名德、众僧，其袈裟缘上绣着四句偈“山川异域，风月同天。
In an interview with students of ancient Chinese literature and professor of arts at the Capital Normal University, Deng Xiaoping Jun, professor of arts at the same day in Wuhan, said in an interview with students of ancient Chinese literature.
寄诸佛子，共结来缘”，可见长屋王此偈对于鉴真起心发愿东渡日本弘法，起了甚深的感动、莫大的作用。
To send all the buddhs together, we can see that Wang Ji was deeply moved and played a great role in appreciating the truth and making a vow to travel to Japan.
偈，就是诗，佛教的诗。
Ji is a poem, a poem of Buddhism.
“山川异域，风月同天”，诗言日本、中国，虽然山川国土，是不同的国家，可是清风明月，我们两国人民同戴一天。
"Mountains and rivers are alien, the moon is the same day." Poetry says Japan and China, although the land of mountains and rivers, is a different country, but the breeze bright moon, our two peoples share the same day.
下文“寄诸佛子，共结来缘”，诗言寄语中国各位佛子，共同缔结未来的美好因缘。
The following words are sent to all Buddhas to tie the knot together. Poetry tells Chinese Buddhists to make a good fortune in the future.
“现在，当中国人民遭受新型冠状病毒肺炎瘟疫之害，日本送来了珍贵的医疗物资，在包装标签下缘书写着：‘山川异域 风月同天’八个汉字，不仅凝聚着自长屋王、鉴真以来中日两国人民的千年情谊，而且以歇后语修辞法，表达了寄诸佛子，共结来缘——寄语中国人民，共结来缘，也就是日本人民希望与中国人民友好下去的当下的美好愿望。
"Now, as the Chinese people are suffering from the new coronavirus pneumonia, Japan has sent precious medical supplies with the words, 'On the same day, the same day and the same day.
”邓小军教授谈及。
to Deng Xiaoping Army.
本文图片均来自微博日本援助湖北↓岂曰无衣，与子同裳这句来自三千多年前的古话浅白且铿锵。
This picture comes from Weibo Japan's aid to Hutchison, which comes from the simple and sonorous old saying of 3,000 years ago.
“岂曰无衣，与子同袍”来自于《诗经》中的《国风·秦风·无衣》一篇。
"Wouldn't it mean to be clothed and robed with the son" comes from "The National Wind Qin Feng Clothing" in the Book of Songs.
全诗如下：岂曰无衣？与子同袍。
The whole poem is as follows: Wouldn't it be clothed with children?
王于兴师，修我戈矛，与子同仇！岂曰无衣？与子同泽。
King Yu Xingshi, repair my spear, and the son with enmity! Do not say clothed? With the son Zanzig.
王于兴师，修我矛戟，与子偕作！岂曰无衣？与子同裳。
WangYu Xingshi, repair my spear halberd, together with the children! Do not say clothes? And children with clothes.
王于兴师，修我甲兵，与子偕行。
Wang Yu Xingshi repaired my soldiers and traveled with his sons.
我们今天引用该诗时赋予它“同仇敌忾，鼓舞士气”的意义。
We quote the poem today as "unflinching the enemy and cheering up the morale".
日本援助大连↓青山一道同雲雨，明月何曾是两鄕这句诗出自王昌龄的《送柴侍御》，这首诗是这样写的：“沅水通波接武冈，送君不觉有离伤。
As dust leaves dust, so do Ming moons. As flowers start to rain, so do they appear in Wang Changling's poem "Send firewood and handyman," which reads: "Yuanshui connects Wugang with you
青山一道同云雨，明月何曾是两乡。
Qingshan with a cloud rain, the moon is where the two townships.
”诗中蕴涵的正是人分两地、情同一心的深情厚谊。
"It is the profound friendship between two places and one heart that lies behind the poem.
日本援助辽宁↓辽河雪融，富山花开；同气连枝，共盼春来10日，日本富山县向辽宁省捐赠了1万枚口罩，而装满口罩的箱子上则印着：“辽河雪融，富山花开;同气连枝，共盼春来。
2007-3-1 15: 23 Dell Fushan County, Japan, donated 10,000 masks to Liaoning Province on Monday, while boxes filled with masks said, "Liao River is melting with rich mountains and flowers; we are eager for spring together.
”据悉，这首诗引用了南朝梁·周兴嗣的《千字文》：“孔怀兄弟，同气连枝。
"It is reported that the poem quotes South Chaoliang Zhou Xing-hei's" Thousand Words ":" The Konghuai brothers are united.
交友投分，切磨箴规。
Make friends, cut the rules.
” 诗中，“同气连枝”比喻同胞的兄弟姐妹。
In the poem, "concord" is used to describe brothers and sisters of one's compatriots.
日本《朝日新闻》也表示，诗句有中日双方一同期盼春天的到来之意。
Japan's Asahi Shimbun also said the verses indicate that both China and Japan are looking forward to spring.
富山县综合政策局长藏堀祐一说：“我知道目前当地对口罩的需求是迫在眉睫的，辽宁省的各位正在面临着困难，我们将给予支持。
"I know there is an urgent need for masks here, and everyone in Liaoning Province is facing difficulties, and we will support them," said Sukei Horiuchi, director of comprehensive policy for Fushan County.
